Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.	Add 2 melted sticks of oleo and 1 teaspoon
butter
extract.
Stir
quickly
and pour into 2 deep-dish, unbaked pie
shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes or until
center
is
set.	Allow
to
cool
before cutting. Makes 2 pies.

title: tarter sauce
directions: Blend and put in jar. Refrigerate.

title: carrots and apples
directions: Stir everything and bake, covered, at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: meemaw's quick pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with powdered sugar and Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker crust and pour cherry pie filling on top.
Chill at least two hours before serving.
Apple, blueberry, peach or other pie filling can be used.

title: potato strips with cheese
directions: Put strips into greased baking dish and pour the milk over them.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover and bake at 425° for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Sprinkle with cheese and parsley; bake, covered, 5 minutes more.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks one at a time and mix well.
Dissolve soda in small amount of warm water, then add 1/2 of buttermilk.
Add to mixture and mix well.
Add rest of buttermilk.
Add vanilla, then add flour.
Beat 150 strokes.
Beat egg whites and add last.
Bake about 1 hour in 300° oven using angel food cake or Bundt pan.
Cake may be eaten as is or may drizzle outside with powdered sugar icing.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix in deviled ham.
Form into ball. Roll in nuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: This recipe is so easy because it's made entirely in the pan in which it is baked.
Preheat to 350°.
Melt butter or margarine in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
(I do this on the top of the stove at a low heat.)
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over the butter or margarine.
Pour condensed milk over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients and press down.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown hamburger and add taco mix according to directions on package.
Mix picante mix and cream cheese together.
Make layers of hamburger, refried beans, picante mix and cheese.
Repeat for 1 more layer.

title: holiday recipe
directions: Take love and loyalty; mix it thoroughly with faith.
Blend in with tenderness, forgiveness and friendship.
Whip it with hope. Always spice it with kindness and understanding.
Sprinkle abundantly with laughter.
Bake it with sunshine and serve it daily with generous helpings and seconds.

title: 1 crust pie crust
directions: Mix flour, Crisco and salt until like small peas.
Gradually add cold water.
Work together but not too much.
Roll out on a floured surface.

title: old fashioned chicken dumplings
directions: Cut shortening into flour, salt and baking powder.
Add milk to make a stiff dough.
Roll very thin and cut in strips and drop into hot broth.
Cook about 10 to 15 minutes slowly.
Do not stir or remove top from boiler until ready to serve.

title: cheese strata
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Place 4 slices in bottom of a well-greased baking dish. Cover bread with cheese, then the remaining bread.
Beat eggs. Add milk and seasonings.
Pour over the bread and allow to stand for 1 hour. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Serve with or without tomato sauce.

title: sour cream twists
directions: Sift flour and salt in a large bowl.
Cut in shortening and butter as for pie crust.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Beat eggs together.
Combine with sour cream, yeast and vanilla.
Add to the flour mixture and mix well.
Let rise in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Sprinkle sugar lightly on breadboard.
Place dough on sugar; sprinkle sugar lightly on dough and roll to 10 to 12-inch square, folding dough into center from either side.
Roll out and repeat the folding job until you have used the entire 3/4 cup sugar.
Cut into strips 1/2-inch wide and 4 inches long.
Twist the strips 3 or 4 times and lay them on an ungreased cookie sheet several inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: deviled crab eggs
directions: Boil eggs and cut lengthwise.
Remove yolks and put yolks into a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Fill holes of eggs with mixture.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except eggs, cheese and chips.
Put chopped chicken, celery, onion, pimento, soup, mayonnaise, salt and juice together in casserole.
Cover with sliced eggs and cheese.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: dry cocoa mix
directions: Mix together the dry milk, sugar, cocoa and salt.
Store in a dry container.
Put 4 to 5 tablespoons mix to 1 cup boiling water. Top with marshmallows.
Makes 32 cups.

title: chocolate sin cake
directions: Toss chocolate chips and pecans in 1 tablespoon cake mix. Beat together remaining ingredients, except topping, for 3 minutes, then fold in chocolate chips/pecan mixture.
Pour into greased, floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Cool on wire rack 10 to 15 minutes.
Place cake on cake plate. Heat topping until warm (not hot) and fluid.
Pour over cake. Serve warm.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Combine remaining tomato sauce, sprinkle of garlic powder, sprinkle of onion flakes and rest of black olives.
Spoon over loaves after baked 25 to 30 minutes.
Drain.
Put cheese on top. Makes 4 large loaves or 16 to 20 small meat balls.

title: banana split cake
directions: Spread over graham cracker crust.
Cover with 3 or 4 slices of banana.
Add large size can of crushed pineapple (well drained). Cover with Cool Whip (large size container).
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup chopped nuts and 1/2 cup halved maraschino cherries. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken noodle parmesan(preparation time: 20 minutes.  cook time: 10 minutes.)
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine soup, milk, cheese and pepper. Add noodles and chicken.
Over low heat, heat through, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: super colossal cinnamon-pecan ring
directions: Grease a 12-inch pizza pan; set aside.
On a lightly floured surface, flatten thawed dough slightly.
Cut each loaf into 4 pieces (8 pieces total).
Form each piece into a rope about 18 inches long.
Brush each rope on all sides with melted margarine or butter.

title: never-fail biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spray pan with Pam.
Roll mixture out and cut as you usually do.
Place about 1-inch apart on pan.
Bake for about 8 to 10 minutes, until brown.

title: pickled beets
directions: Place cooked beets in a pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and cover beets with mixture.
If you have a large quantity of beets, continue adding mixture until beets are covered.
Bring to boil, boil 10 minutes.
If you preserve them you can pack them into prepared jars.
If not, beets are ready to serve.

title: easy cheese danish
directions: Spread 1 can of rolls in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pinch together so there are no spaces.
Cream sugar, vanilla, lemon juice, cream cheese and egg yolk together.
Pour into pan and spread evenly.
Spread remaining can of rolls on top of mixture, pinching together.
Beat egg white and brush on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: california dip
directions: In saucepan, saute the onion and garlic in the butter. Add the tomatoes and simmer for at least 1 hour. Add the chiles and simmer for another hour. Add the cheese. Blend while still on low fire. Serve Hot!

title: strawberry-banana salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Pour half of mixture into 9 x 13-inch dish and chill for 15 minutes. Spread Cool Whip on top of 1st layer.
Add remaining jello mixture and chill until set.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pat onto bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Take out of oven.
Stir, pat down and bake for 5 more minutes.
Repeat.
Stir, pat and bake 2 more times.
Take out 1/3 cup; reserve for topping.

title: watergate cake
directions: Beat all ingredients for 4 minutes.
Put in a tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake in oven for 50 minutes at 325°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Toast bread; break up in a greased pan. Stir in raisins. Break eggs over sugar in a pan and beat. Add milk and vanilla. Pour over bread mixture. Sprinkle brown sugar over mixture. Also sprinkle cinnamon and dash of nutmeg.

title: dirty rice
directions: Simmer celery and onion in 1 cup water for 5 to 10 minutes. Fry sausage and drain.
Drain vegetables.
Mix all ingredients in casserole.
Stir until mixed.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: meat and cheese loaf
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Press into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: quick new england baked beans
directions: Saute in skillet the bacon and onion until onion is almost tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in honey, mustard, salt and cayenne.
Layer half of beans in a 2-quart covered baking dish. Spoon half of honey mixture over beans.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until honey mixture is absorbed.
Makes 8 servings.

title: black-tie red beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except sour cream and chives and place in 1-quart crock or casserole.
Bake, covered at 325° for 1 hour (if too juicy, uncover and cook 1/2 hour longer).
Serve with side dishes of sour cream and chives for topping.

title: matzoh balls
directions: Cream fat and add egg, water and matzoh meal; beat well.
Add seasonings and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: sugarless spice cake
directions: In saucepan, cook raisins in water until water evaporates. Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil; mix well.
Blend in baking soda and flour.
Stir in cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla. Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cake tests done.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: grandmama's fruit cake
directions: Mix butter, eggs, sugar, juices, buttermilk (with the soda in it) and jelly, then add 4 cups flour and put the other 2 cups over the fruit; coat it real well.
Then add all the spices and the butter and egg mixture to the fruit, then add the pecans.
Mix well and bake at 250° for 3 1/2 hours, if using a steeple pan, or less time for loaf pans.
Line bottom of the pans with paper from grocery bags (cut to fit), grease this real good and dust with flour.
Test cakes to be sure if they have cooked long enough.

title: brownies
directions: Mix cocoa and oleo together.
Add sugar and eggs and beat. Add flour, baking powder, salt, nuts and vanilla.
Pour batter into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes. Cool in pan and cut into squares.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: hot rod dog
directions: Heat hot dog as directed on package or grill until thoroughly heated.
Place hot dog in bun to form "body".
Place little wiener upright at one end of hot dog to form "driver", using Cheez Whiz to secure pieces.
Attach cherry tomato to top of little wiener with pretzel stick to form "driver's head".
Place tomato slice, cut in half, upright in hot dog, attaching with a dab of Cheez Whiz in front of driver to form "windshield".
Place singles over hot dog in front of windshield, to form "hood".
Decorate with a squiggle of ketchup.
Attach whole pimento stuffed olives in front of hood to form "headlights".
Attach pickle slices with pretzel sticks; insert both sides of hot dog bun, front and back, to form "wheels". Use cracker to form "steering wheel".
Attach green onion slices (white part) to driver's head using dab of Cheez Whiz, to form "goggles".
Attach ripe olive slice, cut in half, to driver's head, using dab of Cheez Whiz, to form "smile".
Cut olive slice in quarters to form "eyebrows".
Attach pretzel stick to each side of little wiener to form "arms".

title: cherry crumb cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in the butter, then egg to make crumbs.
Put half the crumb mixture in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour cherry pie filling evenly over. Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: In saucepan melt chocolate and butter; add water and unbeaten eggs (one at a time), beating all the time.
Add other ingredients; mix until thickened.
Pour in greased pie pan or square cooking dish.
Let set in oven, then turn oven on 350°. Cook about 30 minutes.
Cut in slices when cooled and serve with scoop of ice cream.

title: spicy barbecue beans
directions: Chop onion.
Combine all ingredients and place in baking dish. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: avocado and shrimp fettucine
directions: In large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon butter over medium heat; add minced garlic and cook for 1 minute.
Add parsley, shrimp and vermouth and cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly, until shrimp turns pink.
Do not overcook.
Transfer to small bowl.

title: cottage cheese meat loaf
directions: In a bowl, combine the first eight ingredients. Add beef and mix well. Press into an ungreased 8-inch square baking pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until meat is no longer pink. Drain. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting. Yield: 4 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Roll in 3/4-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Immediately put Kisses in center of cookies. Remove cookies and place on wire rack to cool.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry sausage until well browned. Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 425° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry-sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add fruit.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in a 11 x 7-inch or 9-inch square pan.
Refrigerate until jelled.
Spread sour cream on top.
Pour remaining Jell-O mixture over cream and refrigerate.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: mama's "t" cakes
directions: Mix
sugar
and
Crisco.
Blend well.
Add soda, baking powder and
vanilla.
Slowly
sift flour into mixture until a soft dough
is
formed.	Divide	dough
onto a pile of flour. Knead until
it
can be rolled out and cut cookies with a jar lid.
Put on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until brown.

title: trudie's wilted mustard greens
directions: Fry middling meat and remove from skillet.
Pour most of grease into bowl and reheat skillet until hot.
Add water and this will make a redeye gravy.
Add to bowl of grease.
Pour immediately over chopped vegetables.
Eat with homemade hot biscuits.

title: quick oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine margarine and sugar; beat until creamy.
Fold in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices; add to mixture and mix well.
Stir in oats.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes for chewy cookies or 10 to 11 minutes for crispy cookies. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet, then place on wire rack.
Yield: Approximately 8 dozen.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken broth and both soups.
Divide all ingredients in half.
In greased casserole dish, put in chicken, sprinkle lightly with chili powder, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Follow with soup-broth mix.
Then onion and green pepper on top. Make layer of tortillas and sprinkle with cheese. Repeat second layer as first. Top with crushed tortilla chips.
Bake, covered, 1 hour at 350°. Serves 8 to 12.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in olive oil. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: louisiana seafood gumbo
directions: Brown flour in hot shortening in a Dutch oven, stirring until smooth.
Combine all
ingredients and let simmer.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: perfect pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pie crust.
Beat eggs slightly, then beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
If using fresh pumpkin, it is juicier than canned pumpkin, so reduce milk to approximately 1 cup.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg.
Combine soda and flavoring to milk.
Add this to butter, sugar and egg mixture.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Roll as thin as possible.
Cut cookies with round cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° to 375° until lightly browned.

title: barbecue
directions: Fry beef and onion until done.
Add all other ingredients except catsup and mustard; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add the rest.

title: creamy chicken and rice soup
directions: Remove skin and bone from chicken.
Cut in 1/2-inch cubes. Melt butter in a 4-quart saucepan and stir in chicken pieces. Cook until tender, turning occasionally.
Add 1 cup water, flavor package from rice, bouillon cubes, parsley and onion.
Bring to a boil and stir until bouillon is melted.
Add rice, mushrooms, remaining water and milk.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Gently fluff rice.
Remove from heat.
Blend in sour cream and garnish with chopped parsley.
Serves 8.

title: chicken tortilla soup
directions: In Dutch oven, heat 2 tablespoons oil to medium heat.
Add tortilla strips; cook 3 to 4 minutes or until crisp.
Remove with a slotted spoon; drain on paper towels.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla in bowl.
Then add flour, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Blend well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese; add Marshmallow Creme.
When well blended, add Cool Whip.
Serve with chunks of mixed fresh fruit.

title: yam oat bake
directions: Put drained yams in buttered casserole.
Mix rest of ingredients together and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: finger jello
directions: In a large bowl combine the gelatins; add boiling water.
Stir until all gelatin has dissolved.
Pour into a shallow pan.
Chill to firm.
Cut into squares or using cookie cutters cut out into different shapes.
This is great for picnics and parties because it can be left out for a long time and will not melt like regular jello.

title: homestyle meat loaf
directions: Combine 1/4 cup gravy with beef and next 5 ingredients.
Shape into 8 x 4-inch loaf in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, heat remaining gravy.
Serve over meat loaf.
Makes 6 servings.

title: golden harvest muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a 4 quart bowl combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and cloves.
Add apples, carrots, coconut, raisins and walnuts.
Mix well.
Add oil, milk, vanilla and eggs.
Stir till moistened.
Fill cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.

title: my favorite recipe
directions: Blend love and kindness.
Alternately add, in small portions, appreciation and pleasant companionship sifted with deserving praise.
Flavor with carefully chosen advice.
Lightly fold in cheerfulness and sorrow.
Pour with tender care into clean hearts. Let bake until well matured; turn out on the surface of society. Humbly ask God's blessings and it will serve all mankind.

title: pork chop potato bake
directions: Sprinkle chops with garlic salt and pepper; let stand 1 hour, then brown chops.
In baking dish, layer potatoes and onions. Salt to taste.
Place browned chops on top.
Mix soup and milk. Pour over chops and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Cook with chopped onion, garlic salt and salt and pepper to taste.
Heat mushroom soup, chicken soup, Ro-Tel and taco sauce in pan.
Mix soup mixture with meat.
Place layer of Fritos in casserole dish.
Alternate layer of meat mixture, grated cheese and Fritos.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, uncovered.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine
all
ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in loaf pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Can also be baked in muffin tins (12) at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Be sure and grease pan or tins.

title: haystacks
directions: In top of double boiler over hot (not boiling) water, melt butterscotch morsels.
Stir in salad oil.
In a large bowl, mix chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Pour on butterscotch and mix thoroughly with a fork.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper on greased cookie sheet.

title: congealed ambrosia salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Add rest of ingredients and chill until set.

title: olmstead manor's peanut butter spread
directions: Blend all together very well.
Needs to be refrigerated, but tastes better at room temperature.
Can be used on bread, crackers or carrot sticks.

title: white clam sauce
directions: In a large skillet or Dutch oven, saute onion, garlic and parsley in melted butter until onion is almost tender; add clams, clam broth, salt, basil and pepper.
Boil one minute.
Cook pasta and serve with clam sauce.

title: italian style meat loaf
directions: Mix in large bowl, hamburg, onions, bread crumbs and cheese and knead by hand to semi-dry mix.
Add egg.
Add Ragu sauce.
Place in large loaf tin.
Cover with Ragu sauce and grated cheese (lightly). Cook at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: pumpkin, oatmeal and peanut cake
directions: Mix by hand and add more powdered sugar, if needed.

title: snow cake with topping
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Put in oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pears in white wine
directions: Wash pears.
Pare and core from blossom end but leave steam intact.
Brush with lemon juice.
Combine wine and sugar in large saucepan.
Bring to boiling, stirring.
Bring until sugar dissolves.
Lower heat; add pears.
Cover.
Simmer 10 minutes or until tender but still firm.
Let pears cool in syrup. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Drain pears.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Blend 2/3 of sauce with cream cheese.
Pat down in pie pan. Top with remaining fudge sauce and nuts.
Cut apples in wedges for dipping.

title: parson's punch
directions: Simmer all ingredients (except orange juice) for 20 minutes in a large Dutch oven. Add orange juice. Strain and discard spices. Serve hot in punch cups or mugs. Makes 4 quarts or 32 (4-ounce) servings.

title: asparagus-pea casserole
directions: Layer.
Bake at 350° or until bubbly.

title: sausage soup
directions: Add the first 5 items; simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add beans; simmer until soup and beans are hot.
Good cooked all day in a slow cooker.

title: peppered rib-eye steaks
directions: Brush steaks lightly with olive oil.
In a small bowl, combine all seasonings.
Sprinkle seasonings over steaks and press into both sides.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Grill steaks, turning once, over medium-hot coals 14 to 18 minutes for rare; 18 to 22 minutes for medium; 24 to 28 minutes for well done.
Place on a warm serving platter; cut across the grain into thick slices. Garnish with orange slices and parsley, if desired.
Yields 8 servings.

title: texas barbecued cheeseburgers
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Shape ground beef into 4 patties.
Brush both sides of patties with soy sauce mixture. Grill to desired doneness.
Top each burger with Cheddar cheese. Cook until cheese is melted.
Serve on buns and top as desired. Recipe may be doubled or tripled.

title: lasagna by ruff
directions: First cover bottom of pan with tomato sauce completely.
Then add ground meat and cheese.
Cover with lasagna noodles (about 4). To start the second layer cover the noodles with tomato sauce, meat and cheese.
Repeat this process until you have run out of meat, cheese and noodles.
All seasonings and vegetables are to be cooked with meat.
Your top layer should be covered with meat, cheese and plenty of sauce so the noodles won't get hard.
Cover and bake at 450° for 45 minutes or until cheese is melted thoroughly.
Feeds 6 to 8 people.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Peel carrots; cut in fourths lengthwise.
Place in heavy skillet and add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat, turning often, until tender and glazed.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook 2 chickens; cool.
Cut up.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth, leaving broth even with spaghetti.
Mix ingredients together except Parmesan cheese and add to spaghetti.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish and top with desired amount of Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes or until casserole is bubbly.

title: baked minute steak
directions: Place minute steaks in glass baking dish.
Mix together soup, water and flour.
Pour over meat.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 40 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Peel, boil and then drain potatoes.
Mash with Carnation milk, margarine, salt and pepper.
Put in a large baking dish. Brown hamburger and onion and drain. Add ketchup, salt and pepper.
Put hamburger in "well" you have made in middle of mashed potatoes. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: finnish pancakes(pannukakku)
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smoothly mixed.
In a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, melt 1/2 cup margarine.
When melted, pour in the egg mixture.
Bake in oven at 450°
for 35 minutes.
Serve with syrup, cinnamon sugar or powdered sugar.

title: grandma's peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, butter and milk to boil in a heavy saucepan. Bring to full rolling boil over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and chips.
Stir until bits melt and mixture is smooth. Add marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and blended. Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Let set until firm, then cut in squares.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Line oven dish with potatoes.
Spread cheese and bacon on potatoes.
Dot butter evenly over.
Pour milk, salt and pepper. Repeat layers until potatoes are used.
End with bacon-cheese layer.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until tender.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: In oblong casserole dish spread cornbread.
Mix melted margarine and chicken broth.
Pour over cornbread.
Mix chicken, chopped celery and onions.
Mix with mayonnaise (enough mayonnaise to make like chicken salad) and spread over dressing.
Beat eggs and 1 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Poke holes so milk and egg mixture will penetrate to dressing layer, too. Refrigerate overnight.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Partially freeze steak, then slice across grain into 2 x 1/4-inch strips.
Dredge steak in flour.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add meat and onion; cook until meat is browned.
Stir in consomme, soup, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes, or until meat is tender. Stir in sour cream; cook just until thoroughly heated.
Serve over noodles.
Yields 8 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: With mixer, blend cream cheese, confectioners sugar and butter.
In another large mixing bowl, blend milk, pudding and Cool Whip.
Blend the two mixtures together.
Crush the bag of Oreos.
In desired serving dish, layer cookies and pudding mixture.

title: topaco
directions: *Your choice of variety: ham, salami, bologna, spiced luncheon meat.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix butter, sugar and syrup together.
Beat eggs separate.
Add eggs to sugar mixture.
Stir, then add coconut. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add buttermilk, oil and eggs. Bake in well-greased pans in moderate oven (350° to 375°). Makes 2 pans.

title: haluski
directions: In a large pot, melt butter.
Add onions and simmer until onions are soft.
Add shredded cabbage.
Salt and pepper to taste. Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally about 45 minutes or until cabbage is very tender.
Add brown sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Add prepared noodles.
(Depending on your taste as little or as much noodles can be added to cooked cabbage.)

title: alan and nancy's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms; break out stems (set aside).
Place caps on cookie sheet.
In large bowl, place stick of butter and melt in microwave for approximately 1 minute.
Add finely chopped mushroom stems, fresh peppers, onion and black pepper; mix.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Remove; add crushed Ritz cracker crumbs.
Mix well and stuff caps.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion, place in bottom of casserole dish. Place cooked potatoes on top of meat.
Place cheese on top of potatoes.
Pour mushroom soup over mixture.
Separate biscuits and place biscuits on top.
Cook until biscuits are brown and casserole is hot and bubbly.
(Amount of each ingredient depends on number of servings needed.)

title: caramels
directions: In an iron skillet over medium-low heat, cook all the ingredients 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour in a greased pan.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Let cream cheese stand for about 10 minutes; cream the butter, cream cheese and vanilla until smooth.
Add your sugar, a little at a time, and mix until smooth.
If sugar is lumpy, you may want to sift before adding to creamed mixture.

title: never-fail peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter an 8x8x2 pan or a 10 3/4x7x1 1/2 pan. In a medium saucepan, stir together sugar, milk and salt. Boil until it forms a soft ball when tested in cold water. Remove from heat; add vanilla and peanut butter. Beat and pour into buttered pan.

title: basic marinara sauce
directions: Heat olive oil in deep 12-inch skillet and saute garlic until tender, but do not burn.
Cut tomatoes into small chunks and add to skillet. Add basil, oregano, parsley, salt and pepper and bring to a low boil for 3 minutes.
Add wine and cook on moderate heat for 15 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand for 15 minutes. Serve over 1 pound of pasta.

title: fried turkey
directions: Mix all together, then baste turkey.
Set 2 days in refrigerator.
Deep fry in peanut oil 3 1/2 minutes/lb. at 375°.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: In a saucepan, bring rhubarb and water to a boil.
Remove from the heat.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved; cool.
Stir in sliced strawberries; chill until it begins to thicken.
Prepare whipped topping according to package directions; fold half into rhubarb mixture.
Pour into crust.
Chill 2 hours or until firm. Top with remaining whipped topping and whole strawberries.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Set oven to 375°.
Beat eggs slightly in 2-quart bowl.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup, melted butter and pecans.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake near center of oven 35 to 40 minutes or until filling is slightly firm. Center of pie may look soft when pie is gently shaken, but will become firm when cool.

title: cheese straws
directions: Sift flour and baking powder into bowl.
Cut in butter, cheese and red pepper as for pie crust using a pastry blender or 2 knives.
Add water and mix well.
Fill cookie press, using star plate.
Form straw on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for approximately 8 to 10 minutes in a preheated 375° oven.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately to cooling rack.

title: party pizza
directions: Chop fine the onions, pepper and garlic.
In saucepan, saute veggies in small amount of oil; add sausage.
Cook, mashing finely to separate.
Cook until done, drain off grease good and add Pizza Quick.
Mix well and cook 10 minutes.
Set aside.
Take rolls from package and slice into 4 or 5 slices each.
Place on cookie tin and put about 1/2 teaspoon pizza mixture on each slice.
Smooth to edge of bread.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
After cookie tin is filled with pizzas, place in hot oven at 400° or broiler to melt cheese.
Remove from oven and serve hot or cold.

title: boiled raisin cake(my mother's recipe, mrs.  granville carey)
directions: Combine the shortening, salt, water, raisins and sugar. Add the
nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Boil mixture for
5 minutes;
cool.
Add together, then mix with the raisin mixture, the
vinegar
and baking soda.
Add the flour.
Bake for about 1 hour.

title: rheba's raisin cookies
directions: Cook raisins and water together for 5 minutes, drain and cool.
While raisins are cooling mix remaining ingredients together, add cooled raisins.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet at 325 degrees for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended. Stir melted chocolate into 1 cup of the batter.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and add seasonings; set aside.
In separate pan, cook onion in small amount of margarine (or spray).
Add tomatoes, soups, milk and chilies to onion.
Line a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole pan with tortilla pieces (enough to cover bottom), then add a layer of soup mixture, a layer of cheese and a layer of meat.
Add another layer of tortillas and continue layering ingredients until all are used.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue ham
directions: Mix catsup, sugar, vinegar and onions.
Pour over ham.
Bake 1 hour in oven, until hot.
Could be heated on top of stove also. Serve on buns.

title: arugula, egg and tomato salad
directions: Pick over the arugula and discard any tough stems.
Rinse well and shake off excess moisture.
Core tomatoes and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Put all the ingredients into a salad bowl.
Toss well and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water until tender. Drain. Arrange stalks in greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 11 1/2 baking dish. Place chicken on top. Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; add curry powder. Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese. Combine crumbs and butter. Sprinkle over all. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix the flour, oleo, sugar and nuts.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: opal(greek fried cheese)
directions: *Kasseri cheese may be purchased at R. Hirts Eastern Market in Detroit.
Or ask your butcher to order it.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if the skin is tough; otherwise, just scrub and rinse.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Use a handle to prevent cutting through the potatoes. Put potatoes in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes. Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake for another 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned and cheeses are melted.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in oil.
Combine catsup, water, honey and steak seasoning.
Pour over chops.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes, turning chops once.
This sauce is also good for outdoor cooking.
Makes 4 servings.

title: country fried chicken
directions: For extra spicy, increase poultry seasoning to 1/2 teaspoon and black pepper to 2 teaspoons.

title: lemon delight
directions: Cut butter into flour until resembles coarse meal.
Stir 1/2 cup nuts into flour mixture.
Press pecan mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar; beat until fluffy.
Fold 1 cup whipped topping
into cream cheese mixture.
Spread over crust. Chill. Combine pudding mix and milk at low speed.
Spread over cream cheese.
Spread
remaining
whipped
topping
on pudding. Sprinkle with pecans or walnuts.
Yields 15 servings.

title: pizza meatballs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together well. Shape into balls, placing 1 cube of Mozzarella cheese in the center of each.
Coat meatballs with flour.
Brown in frying pan. Spoon off grease.
Add pizza sauce.
Reduce heat to a simmer and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cool cooked spaghetti by running cold water over it.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix.
Serve chilled.

title: blueberry banana pie
directions: Bake pie shell according to directions. Place bananas in bottom of crust. Mix Dream Whip and cream cheese until smooth. Pour over bananas. Let chill until firm, then pour pie filling on top. Keep chilled.

title: green apple dip
directions: Mix cheese, sugars and peanuts well to form dip.
Slice apples thin and arrange around the dip.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a bowl.
Put chicken in a casserole dish.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: lazy (snoozing) sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add to a casserole dish; bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Spoon onto bread, buns or favorite crackers.

title: fritos casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Layer chili, corn and cheese.
Put crushed chips on top.

title: banana punch
directions: Bring 6 cups water and sugar to a boil in saucepan. Boil for 5 minutes, cool completely. Add frozen orange juice, 4 1/2 cups water, and pineapple juice to sugar mixture. Puree bananas in blender. Add lemon juice. Add to juice mixture. Pour into 3 large plastic zip-loc bags and freeze at least 12 hours or up to 3 weeks. Thaw 4 to 6 hours before serving. Add one bottle ginger ale to each bag of punch.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and milk together.
Fold in lemon juice.
Drain oranges; cut oranges in small pieces and fold into mixture.
Pour into pie shell.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Cook lasagne noodles according to package directions. Mash the potatoes.
Add cheese to the potatoes and beat with mixer.
Saute onion in margarine until soft. Add 1/3 of the onion and margarine to the potato mixture and salt to taste. Generously butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place a layer of lasagne noodles in dish, then a layer of potato mixture. Repeat, ending with noodles.
Pour butter and onion over all.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° until heated through.

title: chili
directions: Saute first three ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: ranch beans
directions: Brown onion and hamburger together.
Add other ingredients and stir.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 425°.

title: french dip sandwiches
directions: Remove all fat from roast and put roast in slow cooker. Combine all remaining ingredients except bread and pour over roast. Add water to almost cover roast.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or until tender.
Remove meat from broth; reserve broth. Shred meat with a fork.
Cut rolls in halves, spread with butter and grill until brown.
Place meat on rolls; dip in reserved broth while eating.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Note: I use 1 teaspoon baking powder.

title: filet mignon with horseradish gravy
directions: Prepare gravy according to package directions; stir in horseradish and mushrooms.
Set aside.
Heat a heavy, nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until hot.
Add steaks and cook 1 minute on each side.
Steaks will be rare.
Place in a lightly greased 1 quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour gravy over steaks; bake at 350° uncovered, for 15 minutes or until desired degree of doneness.
Garnish, if desired.

title: poptart supreme
directions: Heat Poptart(s) in toaster.
Put pudding in a bowl.
Put the Poptart(s) in the bowl.
Mash together.
Eat!!!

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugar.
Add eggs and cream for 5 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add buttermilk alternating with dry ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Cut crust off 3 slices of bread.
Spread cheese between each slice and top.
Cut in quarters.
Spread on side of each.
Put toothpicks in each one and put on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, put in plastic bag and keep until needed.
Cook frozen for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until nearly done; cool.
Peel and slice in half the long way.
Place in baking dish.
Cook syrup from water, butter, brown sugar and salt; pour over potatoes.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Add 1/2 stick margarine and the cheese.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and add to crushed crackers.
Put broccoli in casserole dish and top with crackers.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour and
1/2 cup sugar until smooth and there are no lumps in
flour.
Add
milk,
margarine and egg yolks; cook over medium heat until
it
begins
to thicken.
Add chocolate syrup and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour
in baked pie shell.
Beat the 3 egg whites with
cup
sugar until stiff peaks form. Put on top of filling and bake at 300° until golden brown.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Mix together
and
press
in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: beef cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in crock-pot on low heat.
While cheese is melting, brown meat and drain.
When cheese is melted, add picante sauce and meat to crock-pot.
Cook on low heat for about 30 minutes.
Mixture can be kept warm in crock-pot for as long as needed.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, soup, salt, pepper and onion.
Pour in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are tender.
Add grated cheese and bake until cheese is melted.
